Reasoning: The paper deals with probabilistic planning problems and presents an algorithm for synthesizing sensors in POMDPs. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of sensors and the interaction with the environment suggests that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The algorithmic approach and the use of SAT instances suggest that the paper may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with planning and decision-making, which suggests that it may also belong to the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
